### Build-a-Bank · Step 20 · Spring events + Kafka (Outbox) + real-time notifications (SSE)
### Watch a transfer flow end-to-end: demand-account → Outbox → Kafka → notification → live SSE push.
###
### Start the pieces (4 terminals):
### 0) Broker (Redpanda, Kafka-API):
###    docker run -d --name bank-redpanda -p 9092:9092 redpandadata/redpanda:v24.2.7 \
###        redpanda start --mode dev-container --kafka-addr PLAINTEXT://0.0.0.0:9092 \
###        --advertise-kafka-addr PLAINTEXT://localhost:9092
### 1) Auth:           ./mvnw -pl services/auth spring-boot:run                                   # 8083
### 2) Postgres:       docker compose -f services/demand-account/compose.yaml up -d               # 5433
### 3) demand-account: SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/demand_account \
###                    AUTH_JWKS_URI=http://localhost:8083/oauth2/jwks \
###                    KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS=localhost:9092 \
###                    ./mvnw -pl services/demand-account spring-boot:run                         # 8082
### 4) notification:   KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS=localhost:9092 \
###                    ./mvnw -pl services/notification spring-boot:run                           # 8084

@auth = http://localhost:8083
@da   = http://localhost:8082
@note = http://localhost:8084

### A) Open a live SSE stream and LEAVE IT RUNNING in a terminal — watch transfers appear in real time:
###    curl -N http://localhost:8084/api/notifications/stream
GET {{note}}/api/notifications/stream
Accept: text/event-stream

### Log in for a token (paste the JWT below).
POST {{auth}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"alice","password":"password"}

@token = PASTE_JWT_HERE

### B) Open two accounts, then transfer — this writes the ledger + an Outbox row in ONE transaction.
POST {{da}}/api/accounts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-A","currency":"USD","openingBalance":200.00}

###
POST {{da}}/api/accounts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-B","currency":"USD","openingBalance":0.00}

### C) Transfer → the relay publishes the Outbox row to Kafka → notification consumes it → your SSE stream
### (step A) prints a "transfer ... completed" event within ~2s (the relay poll interval).
POST {{da}}/api/v1/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":40.00,"description":"rent"}

### D) Or read the recent notifications buffer (newest first):
GET {{note}}/api/notifications

### 🧪 Experiment: send the SAME transfer twice with the SAME Idempotency-Key (Step 14) → money moves once
### AND only ONE notification appears (the consumer dedupes by eventId → exactly-once effect).
POST {{da}}/api/v1/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Idempotency-Key: demo-key-1
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":5.00,"description":"coffee"}
